Review: I really enjoyed this movie, up until it ended. What a weak punch that was. They were going for a kind of more ambiguous "Seeking A Friend For The End Of The World" thing, but it just completely fell flat. The dialogue was actually witty and realistic, characters less so, but I'm really getting sick of these Netflix movies that just end, instead of ENDING. But I'll still watch any piece of media that is about an apocalypse... sidenote: I've been talking about that exact scenario and the society collapse that it would cause for years <3
I was definitely expecting to like this more than I did. Beautiful and great but I was just a bit disappointed.

Movie: The Occupation of the American Mind
Review: Great doc, really cites a lot of reputable news sources from throughout the years, compiles a lot of slip-ups where Israeli officials and news media admit to atrocious acts by Israel, and interviews relevant & credible people and activists, including a former AIPAC writer and Noam Chomsky. It's also narrated by Roger Waters.
